<br>
The way I see it...<br>
<br>
How many new people are going to want to come along with you Thogg?  There always are up and coming players, which could be a better player then yourself.  Do you think they would want to always have sloppy seconds to you just because you have more time played?  I know I wouldn't.  I'd want to have just as much a piece of the pie as you, because what makes you better then this new person?<br>
<br>
<br>
Here is a little information for you.  You know Jorply right?  He was level 20 when i was level 50 Thogg.  Can you honestly tell me you are better then him?  Why should YOU get items over him?  You both are probably some of the best warriors on the server if not in EQ, but Jorply has about 80 days played compared to your 200 something.  <br>
<br>
Lets see, here is another example.  Clyssie and Noriko, a pair of the best clerics in the game.  Haha, they are alternates Thogg.  Noriko's main character she started with is named Redrose and would solo Greater Kobolds in Sol B about a year and a half ago.  Clyssie is also a secondary character of Clystal, a Ranger.  Noriko was level 46 when Kunark came out, and now she sports CiH's first cleric BP at level 59, and I bet she has about 50-60 days played.  <br>
<br>
<br>
That is what is so great about our point system Thogg.  People who put the most effort into our guild, get the most items.  Even though we didn't invent this system(guild Afterlife did), it is by far the most fair system to everyone out there, hands down.<br>
<br>
If you don't think this system is fair, then you really have to think what you want with your group of guildmates.  Do you want to stock all the items on a few people, or do you wish to spread them out, making the guild as a whole better.  Ask anyone in CiH, and we want the guild as a whole better.  We want every member to have their FA weapon, their kunark armor, all of that stuff.  But most of all, we want the guild as a whole be good enough to accomplish anything we set our minds to.<br>
<br>
<br>
I'm kind of looking forward to see what happens when Velious comes out.  I'm hoping that our guild will be fine tuned by then to maybe compete with Afterlife and FoH at the first to kill certain mobs.  Would be kinda cool =)<br>
